<#
.SYNOPSIS
Fetches and displays inspirational quotes from Wikiquote.

.DESCRIPTION
GetQuotes is a command-line tool that retrieves inspirational quotes from Wikiquote. 
It supports both online and offline operation, with features for customizing quote sources 
and display options. Written in Rust, it provides fast and efficient quote retrieval.

.PARAMETER authors
Specify one or more authors to fetch quotes from. Multiple authors should be comma-separated.

.PARAMETER rainbow-mode
Enable colorful display of quotes using rainbow colors.

.PARAMETER offline
Run in offline mode using previously cached quotes. Requires prior cache initialization.

.PARAMETER init-cache
Initialize or update the quote cache for offline use.

.PARAMETER completions
Generate shell completions for the specified shell.

.PARAMETER config
Use custom configuration settings from a specified file.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes
Fetches and displays a random quote.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes --authors "Albert Einstein,Mahatma Gandhi"
Gets quotes from specific authors.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes --rainbow-mode
Displays quotes with rainbow colors.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes --offline
Uses cached quotes in offline mode.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes --init-cache
Initializes the quote cache.

.EXAMPLE
getquotes --completions bash
Generates bash shell completions and prints them.

.NOTES
Author: Muntasir Mahmud
Version: 0.4.0
GitHub: https://github.com/MuntasirSZN/getquotes

.LINK
https://github.com/MuntasirSZN/getquotes

.INPUTS
None. GetQuotes does not accept pipeline input.

.OUTPUTS
System.String. GetQuotes outputs quotes as text.
#>
